==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hygrometer
<hw>Hy*grom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wet,
moist + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F. <ets>hygrom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring the degree of
moisture of the atmosphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Daniell's hygrometer</b></col>, <cd>a form of hygrometer
consisting of a bent glass tube terminating in two bulbs, the one
covered with muslin, the other of black glass, and containing ether and
a thermometer. Ether being poured on the muslin, the black ball, cooled
by the evaporation of the ether within, is soon covered with dew; at
this moment, the inclosed thermometer gives the dew-point, and this,
compared with the reading of one in the air, determines the
humidity.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Hygrometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hygrometric</ent>⟦br⟧
